blockInterval(uint64,uint128,uint128,uin.details: Allow execution on a block interval

params.id: A unique id for the block interval. This id is used to store the block interval state. Use a random id to avoid collisions.
params.initialStart: The initial start block number. Setting this to 0 will allow the first execution to occur immediately.
params.intervalMinSize: The minimum size of the block interval. This is a minimum because the actual interval can be longer if execution is delayed.
params.maxIntervals: The maximum number of intervals that can be executed. Set this to 0 for unlimited executions.
